# Security Rules

## Contact API (`/api/contact/route.ts`)

- **XSS risk:** User input (`firstName`, `lastName`, `message`, etc.) is interpolated into HTML. Sanitize or escape before using in `html` template. Consider a sanitization library (e.g. DOMPurify) or text-only encoding
- **Validation:** Add email format, phone format, max lengths before sending
- **Rate limiting:** Not implemented — consider per-IP or per-session throttling

## Age Verification

- Stored in `sessionStorage`; easily bypassed via DevTools. Document as UX/compliance layer, not enforcement
- Do not assume age gate prevents access to content — content loads before verification

## Environment

- Never commit `.env*` — `RESEND_API_KEY` must stay server-side only
